WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:01.653
.

00:01.697 --> 00:04.134
- Previously on "Good Girls."

00:04.178 --> 00:05.570
- I would suggest we put Sara
on a list for a transplant.

00:05.614 --> 00:07.007
- A girl at Madison
just got hit.

00:07.050 --> 00:08.617
- Jesus.
- Perfect match.

00:08.660 --> 00:09.966
- Are people pulling
your pants down?

00:10.010 --> 00:11.228
- They wanna know what I am.

00:11.272 --> 00:12.708
- We could send her
to St. Anne's.

00:12.751 --> 00:14.492
- She's an atheist who enjoys
a bow tie.

00:14.536 --> 00:16.146
I don't think that Catholic
school is a good fit.

00:16.190 --> 00:17.669
- It's cancer in your prostate.

00:17.713 --> 00:19.671
- Couldn't make it sound
a little more serious?

00:19.715 --> 00:21.064
- Can I call you Big Mike?

00:21.108 --> 00:22.500
- My friends--
[gunshot]

00:22.544 --> 00:24.111
[all screaming]
- You shot me in the foot!

00:24.154 --> 00:25.547
Stay away from me!

00:25.590 --> 00:27.418
Take what you came for
and get out of here.

00:27.462 --> 00:29.203
- Just put the whole thing
on the "I'm what's keeping you

00:29.246 --> 00:30.639
out of jail" account.

00:30.682 --> 00:32.554
- Would you ever want
to grab a coffee?

00:32.597 --> 00:34.904
- I had fun tonight.
Should I put on some tea?

00:34.947 --> 00:37.037
- Yeah.
- Who's the boy?

00:37.080 --> 00:39.256
- That fool we arrested.
He's ours now.

00:39.300 --> 00:40.866
- They have him.
The FBI.

00:40.910 --> 00:43.434
And he is talking to them.
- You think I need you?

00:43.478 --> 00:45.088
Ain't nothing but a damn
charity case to me.

00:45.132 --> 00:46.176
Go home.
- I don't see how

00:46.220 --> 00:47.438
you're gonna let me do that.

00:47.482 --> 00:48.918
- You're sure he's
coming for us?

00:48.961 --> 00:50.224
- We know too much now.

00:50.267 --> 00:51.660
- Maybe we should turn
ourselves in.

00:51.703 --> 00:53.575
It's better than waiting
to be murdered.

00:53.618 --> 00:55.185
- He's the one who should
be in jail.

00:55.229 --> 00:57.361
- Then let's put him there.

00:57.405 --> 01:00.930
[Two Feet's
"I Feel Like I'm Drowning"]

01:00.973 --> 01:03.063
- ♪ Yeah
Uh-huh ♪

01:03.106 --> 01:04.281
♪

01:04.325 --> 01:06.153
♪ You keep dreaming and--

01:06.196 --> 01:08.851
- We hire a hit man.
- Seriously?

01:08.894 --> 01:11.984
- We don't need him dead.
We need him in jail.

01:12.028 --> 01:13.421
-Let me finish.

01:13.464 --> 01:16.598
We hire a hit man,
and then we frame Rio

01:16.641 --> 01:19.557
for the murder that
the hit man commits.

01:19.601 --> 01:21.342
- Oh, well, when you put it
like that, then...

01:21.385 --> 01:24.171
- Who's the hit man gonna hit?
Random innocent?

01:24.214 --> 01:25.824
Someone who cuts in line
at the Starbucks?

01:25.868 --> 01:29.350
- Oh, there are candidates.
- I'm sure there are.

01:29.393 --> 01:31.830
- Look, nobody said this was
gonna be easy, okay?

01:31.874 --> 01:35.182
- If it was,
the FBI would have done it.

01:35.225 --> 01:37.009
♪

01:37.053 --> 01:39.099
- ♪ I feel like I'm drowning

01:39.142 --> 01:43.668
♪

01:43.712 --> 01:46.106
♪ You're killing me slow

01:46.149 --> 01:47.107
♪ So slow

01:47.150 --> 01:48.804
- Mind control.

01:48.847 --> 01:50.632
Turns himself in.

01:50.675 --> 01:53.200
- And I'm done.
- It's called brainstorming.

01:53.243 --> 01:54.766
You throw stuff out,
you see what sticks.

01:54.810 --> 01:56.333
- I've got something
in the morning.

01:56.377 --> 01:58.335
- More important than
being murdered?

01:58.379 --> 01:59.728
- We're meeting with
the finance people

01:59.771 --> 02:03.210
from the hospital.
- What are you gonna do?

02:03.253 --> 02:06.126
- Say, "We can pay for
that kidney, no problem."

02:06.169 --> 02:08.606
♪

02:08.650 --> 02:10.956
Write a bad check and hope
they don't realize

02:11.000 --> 02:12.610
until she's open on the table.

02:12.654 --> 02:14.438
- It's a good plan.
- Go with God.

02:14.482 --> 02:17.963
- ♪ And your friends
all start leaving ♪

02:18.007 --> 02:18.964
♪ You're so plastic

02:19.008 --> 02:20.270
- I'll call you tomorrow.

02:20.314 --> 02:21.967
- Park in your garage,
just in case.

02:22.011 --> 02:23.795
- Yeah, and don't let anybody
pull up next to you

02:23.839 --> 02:25.841
at a stop light.
- How am I supposed to do that?

02:25.884 --> 02:28.191
- Just keep inching forward.
- You know what?

02:28.235 --> 02:29.714
Don't even stop.
- Yeah.

02:29.758 --> 02:30.715
Run the reds.

02:30.759 --> 02:32.456
♪

02:32.500 --> 02:33.631
- Do you wanna just--

02:33.675 --> 02:34.980
- I'll tell Stan
I drank too much.

02:35.024 --> 02:37.287
- It doesn't have to be a lie.

02:37.331 --> 02:39.420
- Yeah, you can crash
on the couch.

02:39.463 --> 02:44.164
- ♪ Slow, so slow oh no

02:44.207 --> 02:47.993
♪ I'm drowning

02:48.037 --> 02:50.996
♪ My life's okay

02:51.040 --> 02:53.477
♪ Yeah just when you're
not around me ♪

02:53.521 --> 02:55.305
- Oh, thanks.
I'm not staying.

02:55.349 --> 03:00.658
- ♪ My life's okay just when
you're not around me ♪

03:00.702 --> 03:03.792
If you're waiting on my boy,
you're wasting your time.

03:03.835 --> 03:04.967
He ain't coming tonight.

03:05.010 --> 03:07.012
♪

03:07.056 --> 03:09.450
Yeah, so, if I were you,

03:09.493 --> 03:12.322
I'd go back home to that
beautiful family in Baltimore.

03:12.366 --> 03:14.498
Let's just call this thing
what it is, yeah?

03:14.542 --> 03:16.370
I mean, not that I mind having
my picture taken,

03:16.413 --> 03:19.373
but it must be getting pretty
old for you people,

03:19.416 --> 03:21.636
chasing my ass all over
the city and not coming up

03:21.679 --> 03:23.507
with jack.

03:23.551 --> 03:24.943
- I think I'll talk
to Eddy myself,

03:24.987 --> 03:25.944
if you don't mind.

03:25.988 --> 03:28.033
♪

03:28.077 --> 03:29.252
- Good luck with that.

03:29.296 --> 03:31.254
♪

03:31.298 --> 03:35.954
- ♪ I'm drowning

03:37.608 --> 03:40.307
- Her match was removed from
life support late last night,

03:40.350 --> 03:43.527
so I'd say we're in
a 24 hour window.

03:43.571 --> 03:46.356
Once we hear,
you sign the consents,

03:46.400 --> 03:47.749
we deposit the payment,

03:47.792 --> 03:50.708
and Sara goes straight
to surgery.

03:50.752 --> 03:53.885
- Um, how much of that
does insurance cover?

03:53.929 --> 03:56.975
- Your out of pocket was 20%
after deductible.

03:57.019 --> 04:02.546
- And that's what now?
- $87,400.53.

04:02.590 --> 04:03.895
- Okay.
- Specific.

04:03.939 --> 04:05.506
[both chuckle]

04:05.549 --> 04:07.856
- So, do you all need us to
write a check now, or--

04:07.899 --> 04:09.553
- That'd be great.
- Yes, right now is--

04:09.597 --> 04:10.598
- Fantastic.
- I can do.

04:10.641 --> 04:11.947
- Not a problem.
- Can do.

04:11.990 --> 04:13.905
- Yeah, we've got that.
- All right.

04:13.949 --> 04:15.559
- [chuckles]

04:15.603 --> 04:17.822
- Of course, my pen runs out.
- It's not--

04:17.866 --> 04:19.694
- Babe, do you have a--
- You know what?

04:19.737 --> 04:23.263
I think I do have a--
No, wait.

04:23.306 --> 04:25.743
You're not a pen.
all: [laughing]

04:25.787 --> 04:27.354
- You cannot write with that.
- You could try.

04:27.397 --> 04:30.052
It's not gonna happen.
- You--you can use mine.

04:30.095 --> 04:31.314
- There we go.
- Okay.

04:31.358 --> 04:34.448
- Yeah.
- Uh, this can be a really

04:34.491 --> 04:36.754
anxious time,
so just be sure you take

04:36.798 --> 04:39.496
some time to practice
self-care, okay?

04:39.540 --> 04:43.239
- Oh, yeah.
- We're all about that Namaste.

04:43.283 --> 04:45.937
- Yes, regularly, yes.
- Great.

04:45.981 --> 04:48.592
- How much is in there?
- $3,500.

04:48.636 --> 04:50.725
- GoFundMe?
- Hang on.

04:50.768 --> 04:52.944
But I think about $1,000.
- Okay, well,

04:52.988 --> 04:55.773
we still got options.
- Like what?

04:55.817 --> 04:57.471
- If corporate comes through,
call them again.

04:57.514 --> 05:00.387
- I already did,
and GoFundMe's at 800.

05:00.430 --> 05:02.389
- [sighs]
I thought you said 1,000.

05:02.432 --> 05:03.825
- I was wrong.

05:05.087 --> 05:06.349
- Okay.

05:06.393 --> 05:07.742
All right, well,
church could do another

05:07.785 --> 05:09.526
car wash or a rummage sale.

05:09.570 --> 05:11.136
I can pass the hat
at the station.

05:11.180 --> 05:12.747
Hell, we can go door to door,
but people are gonna need

05:12.790 --> 05:14.357
to step up.
- They already have.

05:14.401 --> 05:15.663
- Well, they need to step up
their step-up.

05:15.706 --> 05:17.621
- Stan.
- [sighs]

05:17.665 --> 05:18.796
- This check is gonna
bounce so hard.

05:18.840 --> 05:20.320
- I know.
- And it's not just

05:20.363 --> 05:21.451
gonna bounce.
It's gonna ricochet.

05:21.495 --> 05:23.018
- I know.
- It's a two year felony

05:23.061 --> 05:24.976
for writing a bad check, Ruby.
You can go to jail.

05:25.020 --> 05:26.891
- You can go to jail
for a lot of things.

05:28.066 --> 05:30.591
- Well, then, we might as well
just rob a bank.

05:30.634 --> 05:33.463
- All right, just...
- [sighs]

05:33.507 --> 05:35.291
- Calm down.
Okay?

05:35.335 --> 05:36.466
- Mmm-hmm.
- Breathe.

05:36.510 --> 05:40.557
- [sighs]

05:40.601 --> 05:42.733
- Where'd you get French fries?
- Under the seat.

05:42.777 --> 05:44.648
- Give me one, please.
Thank you.

05:44.692 --> 05:46.084
[mimics chewing sounds]
Delicious.

05:46.128 --> 05:51.133
Hey, guess what Wednesday is?
- Trash day.

05:51.176 --> 05:54.658
Hey, you know who that is?

05:55.833 --> 05:58.445
- Um, I don't know.
Maybe the Lee kid.

05:58.488 --> 05:59.837
- I've just never
seen him before.

05:59.881 --> 06:03.972
- Hmm.
Wednesday is our anniversary.

06:05.452 --> 06:06.670
- I know.

06:06.714 --> 06:08.411
- Yeah, it's our
20th anniversary.

06:08.455 --> 06:10.021
- I know.

06:10.065 --> 06:13.285
- I could make a reservation.
I mean, we gotta eat.

06:13.329 --> 06:15.026
- Dean.
- Look, I just--

06:15.070 --> 06:18.160
I think that we have to decide.
Like, if we're not gonna be--

06:19.466 --> 06:22.512
Then we just--We gotta call it.
'Cause right now we're stuck.

06:22.556 --> 06:24.035
We're, like,
in this weird limbo,

06:24.079 --> 06:29.127
and I guess, like, I'm--
I'm saying that I just--

06:29.171 --> 06:31.086
I gotta know.

06:31.913 --> 06:33.697
- I'm sorry,
you need to know what?

06:33.741 --> 06:36.700
- Is it our anniversary,
or just another Wednesday?

06:40.922 --> 06:42.576
Buckle up, guys.

06:49.757 --> 06:51.889
- Hmm.
How bad is it?

06:51.933 --> 06:54.892
- It's only been a week.
- You hate it.

06:54.936 --> 06:56.720
- It's fine.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.679
- Do all the girls own horses?

06:58.722 --> 07:00.289
Does the gym teacher
wear a habit?

07:00.332 --> 07:02.857
Or does she have nun shorts?
- We don't have gym.

07:02.900 --> 07:05.990
- Hey, then it's not all bad.
- Like I said.

07:06.034 --> 07:08.732
- Look, Dad and Nancy just get
to make the decisions

07:08.776 --> 07:10.560
for right now,
but I promise you

07:10.604 --> 07:12.954
you do not have to stay here
for much longer, okay?

07:12.997 --> 07:14.564
- I gotta go.

07:14.608 --> 07:18.438
- Hey, you look dope
in the suit.

07:18.481 --> 07:19.917
Love you.
- Love you.

07:19.961 --> 07:22.659
together: Never put no one
above ya.

07:25.662 --> 07:28.622
[dramatic music]

07:28.665 --> 07:35.933
♪

07:36.717 --> 07:39.502
- Annie bananie.
I want you to meet Sally.

07:39.546 --> 07:42.984
I am grooming her
for assistant manager.

07:43.027 --> 07:45.334
- When did you start here,
Sally?

07:45.377 --> 07:48.032
- Three days ago.
- Huh.

07:48.076 --> 07:49.512
Quite a promotion.

07:49.556 --> 07:51.775
- Well, you know, uh,
some people are born leaders.

07:51.819 --> 07:55.126
And, uh, others aren't.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.867
And, you know,
I'm gonna need to start, uh,

07:56.911 --> 07:59.217
delegating a bit more now.

07:59.261 --> 08:02.525
[pop music plays]

08:02.569 --> 08:04.440
- Why's that?
- If you must know,

08:04.484 --> 08:09.358
I am, uh, dating someone
very special.

08:09.401 --> 08:10.490
- Is she Jewish?

08:10.533 --> 08:15.059
♪

08:15.103 --> 08:16.713
- Is she?

08:16.757 --> 08:22.153
- Uh, so, Annie's drawer was,
uh, 78 cents short last night,

08:22.197 --> 08:23.633
Sally.

08:23.677 --> 08:26.506
- Let me show you how we fix
that around here, Sally.

08:26.549 --> 08:28.856
Watch and learn.

08:28.899 --> 08:29.944
Hmm.

08:31.206 --> 08:33.338
Hmm.
Hmm.

08:33.382 --> 08:36.211
78.

08:36.254 --> 08:39.562
Then...
[beeps]

08:39.606 --> 08:42.043
Hmm, mmm, mmm.

08:45.133 --> 08:46.177
Bada bing.

08:47.744 --> 08:50.181
- Yeah, so you're gonna need
to stay on the checkout girls.

08:50.225 --> 08:53.663
Especially this one so that
the vault matches

08:53.707 --> 08:55.447
end-of-day receipts.

08:55.491 --> 08:59.190
Now, where things can go really
wrong is the seafood counter.

08:59.234 --> 09:02.019
Now, those guys think anything
on ice is a fresh catch,

09:02.063 --> 09:03.630
even if it's been sitting
around since Christmas.

09:03.673 --> 09:06.589
Sally, I can't tell you how
many potential lawsuits

09:06.633 --> 09:08.591
I have settled over crab salad.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.071
- Hey.
- What's going on?

09:10.114 --> 09:11.638
- You scared the hell
out of us.

09:11.681 --> 09:13.857
- I have an idea.
- You cannot text 911--

09:13.901 --> 09:16.251
- When we have a literal fatwa
on our heads right now.

09:16.294 --> 09:19.210
- Unless it's an actual 911.

09:19.254 --> 09:21.691
- Let me know when you guys
are done and it's my turn.

09:23.084 --> 09:25.477
What is the one thing that
we know about this guy

09:25.521 --> 09:27.523
that the cops don't?

09:27.567 --> 09:30.352
- He wears his hoodie funny.
- Like, half on, half off.

09:30.395 --> 09:32.702
- Yeah, make up your mind, bro.
- That's correct.

09:32.746 --> 09:36.227
But he also launders money
at my work.

09:36.271 --> 09:38.578
Which we found out
the hard way.

09:39.796 --> 09:43.583
Hello?
People go to jail for that.

09:43.626 --> 09:44.975
- We could tell
your FBI guy.

09:45.019 --> 09:47.282
- And what do we say when
he asks how we know?

09:47.325 --> 09:50.590
- Uh, we can't exactly say
we robbed the joint

09:50.633 --> 09:52.330
and got more than we expected.

09:52.374 --> 09:54.594
- We don't have
to tell him anything.

09:54.637 --> 09:57.771
We just have to give them
a reason to look.

10:01.122 --> 10:02.602
- Oh, hell no!

10:02.645 --> 10:04.125
- It's already familiar
territory!

10:04.168 --> 10:05.996
- It's right up there
with the hit man idea.

10:06.040 --> 10:07.998
- But all we have to do
is get the vault open

10:08.042 --> 10:09.696
and the cops will do the rest.
- Oh, my God.

10:09.739 --> 10:11.088
Mind control never sounded
so good.

10:11.132 --> 10:12.742
- They'll never see it coming!

10:12.786 --> 10:14.439
I mean, nobody hits
the same place twice.

10:14.483 --> 10:17.007
- Yeah, 'cause it's stupid.

10:17.051 --> 10:19.183
- But it does get
you your kidney.

10:19.227 --> 10:21.185
[rock music]

10:21.229 --> 10:23.231
We would have to take just
enough for Sara

10:23.274 --> 10:25.668
and then leave the rest
for the feds.

10:25.712 --> 10:27.757
- I mean, we could take
a little more.

10:27.801 --> 10:29.716
♪

10:29.759 --> 10:31.152
- Okay.

10:31.195 --> 10:34.677
♪

10:34.721 --> 10:36.636
- Hello, old friend.

10:46.123 --> 10:46.297
.

10:46.341 --> 10:48.909
- All right, so the store
has gotten some major

10:48.952 --> 10:52.042
security upgrades.
- How major?

10:52.086 --> 10:54.871
- Three new eyes in the sky.
- Oy vey.

10:54.915 --> 10:56.830
- Mmm-hmm.
And a brand new vault.

10:56.873 --> 10:59.571
Which is very high-tech.

10:59.615 --> 11:01.486
- What about your boy
from the treehouse?

11:01.530 --> 11:03.880
- Okay, still not my boy.

11:03.924 --> 11:06.361
And he's not working nights
because apparently

11:06.404 --> 11:08.711
he's in love.
- Eww.

11:08.755 --> 11:10.408
- With what?
- [scoffs]

11:10.452 --> 11:12.715
Right?
- What about Tyler?

11:12.759 --> 11:14.586
- No upgrades on Tyler.

11:14.630 --> 11:16.066
Although he did lose
seven pounds,

11:16.110 --> 11:17.764
so he might run
a little faster.

11:17.807 --> 11:22.638
But he just discovered pho.
- It's pronounced "fuh."

11:22.682 --> 11:24.118
- What does pho have
to do with it?

11:24.161 --> 11:25.989
- Longer dinner breaks,
'cause he does the whole

11:26.033 --> 11:29.384
ceremonial Vietnamese thing.
- All right.

11:29.427 --> 11:30.820
That helps.

11:30.864 --> 11:33.823
And there's panic buttons
at each register now.

11:33.867 --> 11:35.999
- Wait, what?
- Yeah.

11:36.043 --> 11:39.089
- They call the cops?
- Or SWAT, National Guard.

11:39.133 --> 11:40.743
I don't know.
We've never used them.

11:40.787 --> 11:42.440
But whoever they are,
they guarantee response

11:42.484 --> 11:44.007
in ten minutes.

11:44.051 --> 11:48.446
And new linoleum floors.
Very slippery.

11:48.490 --> 11:50.448
- Okay, is that it?
- Yes.

11:50.492 --> 11:53.408
Except for the motion detectors
at the loading docks,

11:53.451 --> 11:56.716
which are infrared.
- Oh, sweet Jesus.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.630
- But that's it.

11:58.674 --> 12:00.371
Except for--
- Oh, my God.

12:00.415 --> 12:01.633
What now?

12:01.677 --> 12:05.246
[quirky music]

12:05.289 --> 12:08.728
- Hey, what is that sound
of crazy footsteps?

12:08.771 --> 12:10.947
What, you only love me
for the candy.

12:10.991 --> 12:13.428
Please, put the candy back!
Put the candy back.

12:13.471 --> 12:16.387
Please, please, put it back.
- Surprise.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.128
Can you drop the kids off
at your mother's tonight?

12:18.172 --> 12:20.000
- Yeah, what--what's going on?

12:20.043 --> 12:22.002
- And maybe you should
stay there, too.

12:22.045 --> 12:24.308
- Are you in trouble?
- Yeah.

12:24.352 --> 12:26.746
- I mean,
is it bounce house guy?

12:27.703 --> 12:29.313
- Yeah.
- Oh, my God, Beth.

12:29.357 --> 12:31.228
- But I've got this.
I'm gonna fix it.

12:31.272 --> 12:33.143
And it'll all be over.
- Let me help.

12:33.187 --> 12:35.755
Please, I mean, I've gotta
do something to help.

12:37.713 --> 12:40.672
- Why don't you make
that dinner reservation?

12:40.716 --> 12:42.587
- Really?

12:42.631 --> 12:44.415
Yeah, okay.
I will.

12:44.459 --> 12:46.026
I can do that.
- Yeah.

